  SECRETS SCANNING DESIGN NOTES:
    engine:            gitleaks (must be in PATH)
    invocation:        detect --source <path> --no-git --report-format json
                       --report-path <tmpfile> [--redact] [--config <toml>]
    baseline strategy: manual fingerprint comparison (NOT --baseline-path)
                       to avoid --redact edge cases
    exit codes:        0 = clean, 1 = findings found — both treated as success
    temp file:         written to os.tmpdir(), deleted in finally block
    suppression match: fingerprint first, then file+ruleId pair

